                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d754">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M)/106a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennedy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-12T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 12, 1940—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1746. This Government has purchased approximately 6300 tons of tungsten and 6700
                    tons of antimony from the Chinese Government, for shipment from Haiphong and
                    Saigon, Indochina, where it has been in storage. The United States vessels, <hi
                        rend="italic">Puerto Rican</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Birmingham City</hi>,
                    of the Isthmian Line, will carry these cargoes to the United States; the <hi
                        rend="italic">Puerto Rican</hi> is now loading and the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Birmingham City</hi> will load during the latter part of the month. Please
                    place this information informally before the appropriate British officials and
                    request that British naval officers be instructed to permit the free movement of
                    these vessels.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
